# PBMP No-Invention Rule

Cursor may assist execution, but PBMP controls truth.

## Forbidden

- Adding features not in approved requirements or design
- Changing acceptance criteria without approval
- Inventing API fields, database columns, or UI elements
- Guessing business rules when data is missing

## Required when blocked

Create a gap log entry:

```json
{
  "gap_id": "GAP-REQ-XXX-01",
  "source_requirement": "REQ-XXX",
  "gap_type": "Missing Business Rule",
  "question": "What should happen when ...?",
  "status": "Open",
  "blocks_downstream_stage": "Development",
  "owner": "Business Analyst"
}
```

Save to `pbmp-implementation-pack/gaps/gap-log.md`.

## Deviation report (end of every task)

Report: requested items, changed items, missing items, extra items, assumptions, tests run, traceability links.
